        <content><![CDATA[    <h1 class="title topictitle1">Create a Discovery schedule</h1>        <div class="body taskbody">        <div class="section context">You can use a Discovery schedule to launch probes, sensors, and pattern operations            for a range of IP addresses, at any time of day, and on a specific interval. You can            also specify the method that is used to select a MID Server.</div>        <ol class="ol steps"><li class="li step">                <span class="ph cmd">Complete the Discovery Schedule form.</span>            </li><li class="li step">                <span class="ph cmd">Right-click in the record&#39;s header and select <span class="ph uicontrol">Save</span> from                    the context menu.</span>            </li><li class="li step">                <span class="ph cmd">To create a range of IP addresses to discover, click <span class="ph uicontrol">Quick                        Ranges</span> under <span class="ph uicontrol">Related Links</span>.</span>            </li></ol>    </div>    <div class="related-links"><div class="relinfo"><div class="reltitle">Related information<br /><div><a class="link" href="https://docs.servicenow.com/?context&#61;CSHelp:CreateDiscoverySchedule&amp;version&#61;kingston" target="_blank">Create a Discovery schedule</a></div></div></div></div>]]></content>
